result.execSummary:
The defendant Cathy J. Maki was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Pursuant to the Supreme Court's Order Issued 4/13/2020, this document is deemed filed 03-17-2021 because that is the date it was mailed.
Appeal form, Written Explanation and JU, NEJ & NOC mailed to defendant at Taycheedah Correctional Institution

03:45 PM Defendant Cathy J. Maki in court, in custody Taycheedah Correctional Institution.  Elizabeth R. Gebert appeared for the State of Wisconsin. All parties via zoom. 16CF28 SAR, Ct's 1, 2, & 4 & 16CF42 Ct's 1 & 3.  Def. would like to proceed without an attorney.  Court goes over waiver of atty right with def.  Court accepts waiver and finds freely & voluntarily given and finds def. is competent to represent herself.  State has reviewed revocation packet and no correction.  Def. reviewed revocation packet.  State gives sentencing argument 16CF42 Ct 1 18 months initial confinement &  18 months extended supervision concurrent Ct 3 90 days jail, 16CF28 Ct 1 18 months initial confinement 18 months extended supervision,  Ct 2 9 months jail, ct 4 90 days jail. All sentence concurrent.  Defendant makes statement. Court orders  16CF42 Ct 1 3 years prison 18 months initial confinement &  18 extended supervision concurrent 
Ct 3 90 days jail, Court obligations converted to civil judgment.  
16CF28 Ct 1 3 years prison, 18 months initial confinement & 18 months extended supervision,  
Ct 2 9 months jail,
Ct 4 90 days jail, All 5 sentence concurrent with each other and any other sentence serving. Court obligations converted to civil judgment. 405 days credit on each case.  Def. is not eligible for Challenge Program and is eligible for Earn Release program. Def. advised of firearm and voting rights.  Def. advised of postconviction rights, COC to mail form.  State has complied with victim rights.

records.addlTxt:
Court calls 16CF28 & 16CF42 @ 11:07 am. Defendant Cathy J. Maki in court, in custody with attorney Alexander Paul Seifert.  Elizabeth R. Gebert appeared for the State of Wisconsin. State gives plea agreement, 16CF28 plea to both ct's 1 & 2, DRI ct 3, plea to ct 4, 16CF42 ct 1 plea, ct 2 DRI, ct 3 plea, ct 4 DRI, ct 5 DRI, Agreement on both case withheld sentence 2 years probation, concurrent, costs, DNA surcharge and comply with terms or conditions under extended supervision. Atty Seifert and def. agree to plea agreement.  Plea questionnaire and waiver of rights filed.  Def. understands charge & penalties. Court backs up on procedures.    Defendant waives right to preliminary hearing.  Court accepts waiver and finds probable cause and binds over.  Informations filed electronically as charged.  Atty Seifert does not have copy of informations, but will continue and  waives reading of information. 16CF28 Ct 1 OMWOC, Guilty plea,  Ct 2 Violate TRO, Guilty plea, Ct 4 D.C., Domestic, Guilty plea & 16CF42 Ct 1 Bailjumping, Guilty &  Ct 3 D.C., Domestic, Guilty.  State will grants State motion DRI and consider for sentencing on ct 3 in 16CF28 & ct's 2 4 & 5 in 16CF42.  Def. advised of constitutional rights & J.T. rights.  Def. understands elements.  Atty Seifert is satisfied. Court finds pleas are freely & voluntarily given.  Factual basis.  Court finds factual basis, accepts plea and finds def. Guilty to 16CF28 Ct 1 OMWOC, Ct 2 Violate TRO, Ct 4 D.C., Domestic  & 16CF42 Ct 1 Bailjumping Ct 3 D.C., Domestic. State request Court to adopt joint recommendation.  Victim rights complied. Atty Seifert ask Court to adopt joint recommendation. Def. makes statement.  
Court orders on 16CF28 Ct 1  withheld sentence 2 years probation, costs and 250 DNA surcharge and comply with all terms of conditions under extended supervision. Sentence are to run concurrent to any other sentence currently serving and each other. Same sentence on all ct's Ct 1 2 & 4 Ct 1 & 3. 30 days to determine credit. No credit but if revoked will have to figure credit. 16CF42 Bond returned to poster.  Bond in 28 applied to costs.   Def. advised of firearm and voting rights.  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Def. advised of postconviction rights. DNA Sample already provided and DNA surcharge only on ct's 1 on each case, waive DNA Surcharge on other ct's.
